Further investigating we found information - "All the clients of the external services are in the "Schemas" module of the CVS (path: IberiaIndra/Schemas). We are further investigating. 12/1/2017 4:15:14 PM, NIIT.rjha, We got few more PNRs from Dale on which we are investigting further. Additionally we requested few PNRs where routes not including MAD. Could you please help us by providing some steps/links to compare the data. May we get the xReagent details so that we can retrieve a Shopping basket booking to compare these timings with the timings of booking manager in ibcom portal. Could you please suggest. column11: Issue : Boarding passes not getting printed after finishing the process. Impact : End users were facing problem to get their boarding passes. Resolution: Issue was due to weather information , which was fixed after changing in Java files. 1/3/18 2:59:14 PM, NIIT.mbajpai, Change has been deployed successfully under CRQ000000106536 change. [12/14/2017] NIIT.SKULYANA, Done and tested the code fix in my local. [2017/12/13] LEDA.jvelasco: Se adjunta correo de Negocio en respuesta al equipo técnico. [12/11/2017] NIIT.SKULYANA, Sent Email to Business asking for Functional Clarificcation. 12/11/17 1:38:40 AM, NIIT.HPANDEY, We received the call from Amadeus and they are investigating the issue. We have provided them multiple JSession ids for which the issue is occurring. 12/11/17 12:31:02 AM, NIIT.HPANDEY, we have raised an P2 IR to Amadeus with below details-: When we further checked it further we found that while the issue is specific mainly for US flights which is due to the missing weather information during printing the Boarding pass.When the boarding pass is being printed, it calls Amadeus service to check and print the weather information for 5 days. We see the information which is coming for Amadeus side should have the data of the weather information for five days. Now when printing the boarding pass while check-in the US routes,the weather information is missing for any of the day(s) and thus it is not allowing to print the boarding pass which is as per the application design. For the routes other than US which we checked like Barcelona and Zurich we are getting correct information in the response. Hence we have raised an P2 IR to Amadeus and downgrading the priority.

column11: Technician Name: Günther Geisse Date: 01/04/18 Travel Start: 07:00 lt Arrive Onsite: 09:15 lt Repair Start: 09:25 lt Repair Stop: 16:15 lt Leave Site: 16:30 lt Travel Stop: 19:00 lt Pre-task: N/A Distance/Travel Time: 24km/5 Hours Details what was done: Arrived onsite to perform maintenance tests for Okidata ML 320 Turbo printer, removed pieces of paper that were stuck inside which were causing new printouts to also be stuck. Software test was done, hardware test was fine. Software test failed and indicated an error between PC/Printer communication. Even though the printer works fine, it will not print. Tested another printer of the same brand (Okidata) that works on another PC, and it is also not printing. The issue is not with the printer itself but with the PC. After numerous tests FE could not find the cause of the printing issue/error. The following tests were done: - Reinstallation - Compatibility mode - Alternative drivers - Alternative emulators - Cabling change (parallel & usb) - Various CPU configurations - Various device configurations All of the aforementioned tests failed. LCON left the site at 15:00 lt, alternative/backup support personnel stayed onsite to assist but they could only stay for 1 hour which I used to work on the equipment. Service is pending as a new ETA is needed from LCON. Please note on 12/01 we got confirmation that there is no issue with the Okidata printer, the problem us with the PC and Mr Burgos, user confirmed he will raise another case to get the PC check. This case can be closed.”

La información del pantallazo de ejemplo que se muestra con trayectos SFO en lugar de OAK sale de la tabla TBILCUP, y por lo que vemos, los datos de esa tabla se dan de alta vía online (Alta de Trayectos), con lo que en principio no se trataría una incidencia del sistema, sino en todo caso de un error humano. Mostramos algunos casos recientes con fecha y hora de inserción, ya que parece un error generalizado, por si ayuda en algo: CUP_BILLETE CUP_CUPON CUP_ORIGEN CUP_DESTINO CUP_CUENTA CUP_EST_CUPON CUP_VIA CUP_CLASE CUP_USER CUP_TIMESTAMP ------------ --------- ---------- ----------- ---------- ------------- ------- --------- --------------- --------------------------- 2374262165 02 SFO BCN S EM W P09P0003 26/12/17 12:42:30,066940000 2374262188 02 SFO BCN S EM W P09P0003 26/12/17 17:12:17,642989000 2374396894 02 SFO BCN S EM Y P09P0003 26/12/17 20:41:07,483608000 2374397200 02 SFO BCN S EM Y P09P0003 27/12/17 16:54:07,502119000 Otra cosa que sí vemos es que cuando se recibe la información de los vuelos reales ésta se cruza con la información cargada en esta tabla, obteniéndose ficheros de salida diarios con aquellos cupones con discrepancias. El caso del ejemplo salió en el fichero del 8 de Julio para el 2º cupón por ejemplo: /datos/ibe/EP09/EP09.BAT06.ERRONEO.V170707 237175140501 FI2621 BCN OAK 2017-06-30 BCNSFO 237176918401 FI2621 BCN OAK 2017-07-02 BCNSFO 237157764901 FI2622 OAK BCN 2017-07-02 SFOBCN 237157765001 FI2622 OAK BCN 2017-07-02 SFOBCN 237157765101 FI2622 OAK BCN 2017-07-02 SFOBCN 237175140502 FI2622 OAK BCN 2017-07-02 SFOBCN 237131823902 FI2622 OAK BCN 2017-07-04 SFOBCN 237166868202 FI6342 GUA SAL 2017-07-04 GUAMAD 237166868302 FI6342 GUA SAL 2017-07-04 GUAMAD No sé si teníais conocimiento de estos ficheros, pero quizás os pudieran sirvar de ayuda para detectar casos cómo estos. column6: LINUX_sun - ibclogec1.ib : Swap area occupied 93.43%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGrou
column11: Issue: Swap memory was almost full on client node Ibclogec1.ib. Later, we received alerts for swap memory memory on second client node. Analysis: Elasticsearch client nodes having a light memory leak and after running for 1 or 2 months, they start consuming swap space quickly. Hence it is required to restart ES services the client nodes in every approx 2 months. Business Impact: If a client node leaves the cluster than it would impact kibana visualization and users will not be able to make requests through kibana. Resolution: Restarted elastic search services on client node Ibclogec1.ib and than on client node (Ibclogec2.ib)

column11: Issue : Boarding passes not getting printed after finishing the process. Impact : End users were facing problem to get their boarding passes. Resolution: Issue was due to weather information , which was fixed after changing in Java files. 1/3/18 2:59:14 PM, NIIT.mbajpai, Change has been deployed successfully under CRQ000000106536 change. [12/14/2017] NIIT.SKULYANA, Done and tested the code fix in my local. [2017/12/13] LEDA.jvelasco: Se adjunta correo de Negocio en respuesta al equipo técnico. [12/11/2017] NIIT.SKULYANA, Sent Email to Business asking for Functional Clarificcation. 12/11/17 1:38:40 AM, NIIT.HPANDEY, We received the call from Amadeus and they are investigating the issue. We have provided them multiple JSession ids for which the issue is occurring. 12/11/17 12:31:02 AM, NIIT.HPANDEY, we have raised an P2 IR to Amadeus with below details-: When we further checked it further we found that while the issue is specific mainly for US flights which is due to the missing weather information during printing the Boarding pass.When the boarding pass is being printed, it calls Amadeus service to check and print the weather information for 5 days. We see the information which is coming for Amadeus side should have the data of the weather information for five days. Now when printing the boarding pass while check-in the US routes,the weather information is missing for any of the day(s) and thus it is not allowing to print the boarding pass which is as per the application design. For the routes other than US which we checked like Barcelona and Zurich we are getting correct information in the response. Hence we have raised an P2 IR to Amadeus and downgrading the priority.

Root Cause: El sistema de recepción de ficheros, cuando el fichero es muy grande, cataloga el fichero antes de que esté completamente transmitido y lanza el proceso finalizando con error al faltar parte del fichero. Steps Taken: Se revisa que el fichero ya lo tenemos completo, se cataloga nuevamente forzando la ejecución del proceso que finaliza correctamente, borrando el fallado.

Issue: Swap memory was almost full on client node Ibclogec1.ib. Later, we received alerts for swap memory memory on second client node. Analysis: Elasticsearch client nodes having a light memory leak and after running for 1 or 2 months, they start consuming swap space quickly. Hence it is required to restart ES services the client nodes in every approx 2 months. Business Impact: If a client node leaves the cluster than it would impact kibana visualization and users will not be able to make requests through kibana. Resolution: Restarted elastic search services on client node Ibclogec1.ib and than on client node (Ibclogec2.ib)

Error 404 is the error thrown by the server side where the application is hosted. This error is seen due to several intermittent reasons, may be the resource is busy or the response time from the server was not right or the browser’s cache is not cleaned, page is not available at server, URL typed is wrong etc. Please suggest user to try again this after clearing the device cache or with different mobile browser and let us know there are any issues. Awaiting for the response.

column6: INCIDENCIA NETTING - RE: FACTURA MELIA COMPENSACIÓN - RITM0830575
column11: Hi Team, We’ve been reviewing the invoices and if you realize the total amount is 0, because in AP we have +30.250 and in AR -30.250, so it supposes that it’s balanced. Anyway, we’ve been looking for information in Oracle Standard Support about this issue and we have found the following information: “No transactions were selected for netting since there were no outstanding balances in AP and AR. Hence, No transaction has been selected for related supplier/ supplier site and related customer / customer site hence, validation failed. Please check the outstanding balance. If there is no outstanding, there is no need for the Netting batch.” So, if there is no outstanding amount it won’t be created, are you sure that aren’t there more transactions? Because if we have one transaction in AP and one transaction in AR with the same amount it won’t be created..

Steps Taken: Búsqueda de la procedencia del la suma de distancias ortodromicas. Correción del fichero EA18.TRASDES.V1712 para los tramos afectados con la distancia correspondiente. Relanzar el proceso desde el principio. Termina OK.

column6: Caida capacidad por falta de vuelos
column11: el problema viene dado porque la captura de datos que se lanza a las 20:00, coincidió con el proceso de actualización de inventario (Schedule). El Schedule no suele correr a esas horas, pero a causa de una carga de vuelos masiva que se había enviado ese día y previendo que podía causar problemas durante el proceso nocturno, se lanzó más tarde de lo previsto, solapándose con el proceso de captura de datos. Para que un vuelo se envíe a Pros tiene que estar consolidado en el inventario, los vuelos indicados fueron procesados con posterioridad a las 20:00 por lo que no fueron enviados en ese fichero pero sí en el siguiente

column11: Issue: Application Iberia Agencies giving error intermittently Analysis: We checked the log files and found fatal errors related to weblogic server. Resource limit exception was found in logs that indicated the the number of resources available in the server are not enough to handle the incoming requests Impact: Downtime of Iberia Agencies application causes revenue loss to Iberia as the agencies are not able to make group bookings and refund requests Resolution: Due to the ongoing campaigns in Iberia, the traffic was high and the application was not able to withstand the situation. We worked with DBA and Weblogic team and increased the maximum connection limit from 25 to 35 in weblogic server, which resolved the issue --------------------------------------------------------------- Duplicate of INC00000097247 and we are monitoring it.. ------------------- Got confirmation from Tomas that Iberiagencias is working fine now. However, we are still monitoring the application and request business to let us know in case of any issue. column11: Issue: Swap memory almost full on client node Ibclogec1.ib Analysis: As elastic search services as build on Java. There is always some memory leak on the client nodes as a result after sometime the swap memory starts to be build up on client nodes. Business Impact: In case swap memory is almost full the client node may leave the ELK cluster and will not be able to take requests from Kibana. Resolution: Restarted elastic search services on client node Ibclogec1.ib.

column11: The SAP order 4100075910 is generated for the WO.4387190. Closing the INC

Buenas Tardes Podemos observar que la publicación se realizó pero las órdenes no fueron creadas. El problema es que el WP fue planeado el 08.01.2018 y fue en enviado a SAP el día de hoy (09.01.18). Como SAP no permite la creación de órdenes cuando la fecha de planificación del WP es menor a la fecha actual. Las órdenes para este WP no fueron creadas. Pudimos observar que el WP todavía está abierto en AMOS que significa que el trabajo no ha sido completado. Por favor cambie la fecha de planificación de la revisión a la fecha de ejecución del trabajo actual y publíquela nuevamente desde AMOS. Déjenos saber si necesita alguna otra ayuda de nuestra parte

1/25/2018 7:06:47 PM, NIIT.prani, Issue Description : Payment refused in Mexico Market Business impact : It has an impact on payments of MX market. Action taken : As issue has resolved long back and temporary solution has been provided for alert part, we are resolving this incident. We are working on the permanent solution for alert and chasing for RCA with netplus team paralally. Relevant mails are attached for the reference. Issue: ERROR: “Error bancario. El banco devuelve un mensaje que no se puede procesar”.was occurring in Mexican market since January 04,2018 (however reported on 9th Jan) and it was happening on the NETPLUS payment gateway with Visa and Master Card so was raised to Netplus on 9th. An estimated 23% transactions were impacted. Resolution: Netplus have confirmed that they are not seeing the error any more from Evalon post 10 Jan 2018 19:51:32. Yesterday, Service got deactivated as the no. of errors were high. However, no alert was triggered (we are checking the reason why, as alerts for other markets are being received). As a workaround, below mentioned changes were made in the HOT table for service continuation yesterday and will continue this until the alert is in place and confirmation receive from all parties that MX payments are stable. • Threshold limit has increased to six times. • Auto activation switch has been enabled. • Time window for Auto-activation is kept to 30 Minutes. • We will also keep a watch over the service in HOT table manually over different intervals. [1/19/2018 ] NIIT.abansal, Netplus has not confirmed yet about RCA of the issue, mail sent yesterday,a awaiting response. 1/9/2018 5:40:17 PM, NIIT.prani, We have sent the below to netplus. Mail is attached for the reference. "We have the following error in the payment in the Mexican market; rejection message “Error bancario. El banco devuelve un mensaje que no se puede procesar”.This error has started to occur on January 4,2018. It is happening on the NETPLUS payment gateway with Visa and Master Card. Please have a look. Impact: 20 PNRs of average per day."

column6: Fallo Software: PAGINA WEB DE IBERIAGENCIAS NO FUNCIONA
column11: Issue: Application Iberia Agencies giving error intermittently Analysis: We checked the log files and found fatal errors related to weblogic server. Resource limit exception was found in logs that indicated the the number of resources available in the server are not enough to handle the incoming requests Impact: Downtime of Iberia Agencies application causes revenue loss to Iberia as the agencies are not able to make group bookings and refund requests Resolution: Due to the ongoing campaigns in Iberia, the traffic was high and the application was not able to withstand the situation. We worked with DBA and Weblogic team and increased the maximum connection limit from 25 to 35 in weblogic server, which resolved the issue --------------------------------------------------------------- Duplicate of INC00000097247 and we are monitoring it.. ------------------- Got confirmation from Tomas that Iberiagencias is working fine now. However, we are still monitoring the application and request business to let us know in case of any issue. Mail below for reference. --------------------------- From: NIIT.Chaudhary Abhishek, Chaudhary Abhishek Sent: Tuesday, January 09, 2018 8:59 PM To: Parejo Sánchez, Tomás <tparejo@iberia.es>; Velasco Bernal, Paz <PVelasco@iberia.es>; Celaya Cerdán, Ángeles <macelaya@iberia.es> Cc: Gil López, Carmen Montserrat <cmgil@iberia.es>; Del Valle Moreno, Maria Esther <mevalle@iberia.es>; López Izquierdo, Carmen <mclopezi@iberia.es>; Valladar Mínguez, José Ángel <javalladar@iberia.es>; NIIT.Rico Palomino, Francisco <NIIT.frico@iberia.es>; SupportProfessionalWeb <SupportProfessionalWeb@iberia.es>; Soporte Sistemas Iberia (Help Desk 74700) <ssi@iberia.es> Subject: RE: PAGINA WEB DE IBERIAGENCIAS NO FUNCIONA. Hola Tomás, Gracias por su confirmación.. Infórmenos en caso de que tenga algún problema al acceder a Iberiagencias. Issue: Application Iberia Agencies giving error intermittently Analysis: We checked the log files and found fatal errors related to weblogic server. Resource limit exception was found in logs that indicated the the number of resources available in the server are not enough to handle the incoming requests Impact: Downtime of Iberia Agencies application causes revenue loss to Iberia as the agencies are not able to make group bookings and refund requests Resolution: Due to the ongoing campaigns in Iberia, the traffic was high and the application was not able to withstand the situation. We worked with DBA and Weblogic team and increased the maximum connection limit from 25 to 35 in weblogic server, which resolved the issue ----------------------------------------------------- Duplicate of INC00000097247 and we are monitoring it.. ------------------- Got confirmation from Tomas that Iberiagencias is working fine now. column6: GRU004: Error in GREXDWH daily load
column11: Issue: Error in GREX dataware house daily load. Analysis: GREX daily load failed as the files from 11th Jan to 17th Jan were not received from the Source team 'NIIT_MTO_GESING'. We have raised an incident for the source team and coordinated for the missing dates files. Business Impact: Users will not be able to see data in OBI reports for the missing dates. It will impact the reports users are making in order to take decisions based on group bookings. Resolution: There was an issue with source team system as they were not able to send the daily files. Once we received all the missing dates files from the source team, we reprocessed the daily load in ODI load plan: LP_GREXDWH_CARGA_DAILY and checked logs for successful execution of the reports.
Se informa al usuario del proceso de seguridad.

Issue: Application Iberia Agencies was giving error intermittently Analysis: We checked the log files and found fatal errors related to weblogic server. Resource limit exception was found in logs that indicated the the number of resources available in the server are not enough to handle the incoming requests Impact: Downtime of Iberia Agencies application causes revenue loss to Iberia as the agencies are not able to make group bookings and refund requests Resolution: Due to the ongoing campaigns in Iberia, the traffic was high and the application was not able to withstand the situation. We requested weblogic team to restart the application and also DBA team to kill all the Inactive sessions. The issue was resolved after weblogic and DBA performed the tasks ------------------------------------------------------------- We have verified the application and it is working normal now. We have asked the Business to verify from their end and confirm.

column6: SIC011: Incidencia sobre algoritmo de Forward Revenue
column11: He ejecutado la consulta en varias ocasiones y no consigo que me devuelva el error. ¿Siempre se usan los mismos filtros? Creo que el problema puede venir por el comportamiento de OBIEE al exportar a texto plano. En la consulta que me mandas el total de filas gira en torno a las 9000 sin embargo al exportar se acerca más a las 11000. Esto se debe a que en el texto plano se muestran los datos sin agrupaciones, una fila devuelta por la base de datos por una en el fichero, además de hacer de nuevo la consulta a la base de datos para traer los registros en detalle. Si alguna de las consultas es distinta puede acercarse al límite de filas exportables o tiempo de permanencia de la query en la base de datos.

column11: Issue: Ha fallado el proceso I19O046. Impact: Se retrasa la carga de la información que contiene el fichero. Root Cause: El sistema de recepción de ficheros, cuando el fichero es muy grande, cataloga el fichero antes de que esté completamente transmitido y lanza el proceso finalizando con error porque el fichero recibido no esta completo. Steps Taken: Verificación las distintas ejecuciones del proceso para comprobar que exista una ejecución correcta. Se borra el proceso fallado.

El error viene por el agente que introduzco la tarjeta en el sistema, el cual puso la credit card con 16 dígitos. BAP 1,CC1766640999461022,0122 Evidentemente para nosotros es imposible saber qué dígito es el que puso de más, El número de token se genera a partir de la credit card introducida, si se introduce mal, el token se generará mal, con los mismos digitos que la tarjeta. 1000001771271022 Por nuestra parte no podemos decirdir si se pasa a perdidas o no. Contactar con el departamento funcional para estas consultas. Help Desk PSS RESTKT <IBPSS.HDRESTKT@iberia.es>; DS/PSS COORD <pss.coord@iberia.es>

Buenos días Javier, Después de revisar este caso vemos que existen 3 movimientos de 775000000 JPY en la cuenta 57348000. A continuación los 3 asientos: COMENTARIOS ACCOUNT CP DB PERIOD NAME CURRENCY CODE ENTERED_DR ENTERED_CR ACCOUNTED_DR ACCOUNTED_CR CURRENCY CONVERSION_DATE CURRENCY CONVERSION_RATE CURRENCY CONVERSION_TYPE DESCRIPTION DESCRIPTOR PERIODO PRESUPUESTARIO CENTRO_DE TESORERIA PAIS JOURNAL_NAME BATCH_NAME JE_HEADER_ID Movimientos de creación del cobro IB66893 57348000 CP69001A 101 07-17 JPY 775000000 6235882,5 31/07/2017 1 User 75554 00000IB66893 07-17 CG000100 JAPÓN 31-JUL-2017 101 JPY Cuentas a Cobrar A 637020 16742987 1999844 57700308 CP09082A 101 07-17 JPY 775000000 6235882,5 31/07/2017 1 User 75554 CP09082A2807 07-17 CP69001A JAPÓN 31-JUL-2017 101 JPY Cuentas a Cobrar A 637020 16742987 1999844 Movimientos de reversión del cobro IB66893 57348000 CP69001A 101 08-17 JPY 775000000 6235882,5 04/08/2017 1 User 75554 00000IB66893 07-17 CG000100 JAPÓN 04-AGO-2017 101 JPY Cuentas a Cobrar A 642001 16774315 2002122 57700308 CP09082A 101 08-17 JPY 775000000 6235882,5 04/08/2017 1 User 75554 CP09082A2807 07-17 CP69001A JAPÓN 04-AGO-2017 101 JPY Cuentas a Cobrar A 642001 16774315 2002122 Otro cobro que tiene el mismo código IB66893 57348000 CP69001A 101 08-17 JPY 775000000 5989963,38 31/08/2017 1 User 77910 00000IB66893 07-17 CG000100 JAPÓN 31-AGO-2017 101 JPY Cuentas a Cobrar A 644006 16810507 2003320 57700302 CP09064A 101 08-17 JPY 775000000 5989963,38 31/08/2017 1 User 77910 CP09064A2807 07-17 CP69001A JAPÓN 31-AGO-2017 101 JPY Cuentas a Cobrar A 644006 16810507 2003320 Como se observa, el tipo de cambio es 1 y el tipo es “Usuario”. Esto ocurre cuando en la importación del asiento en GL, el importe en moneda local viene ya informado (no se calcula con el tipo de cambio), por lo que en este caso la fecha del tipo de cambio informada en GL no es la real. El tipo de cambio real de los cobros se aplica en el módulo de Contabilidad Auxiliar (SLA) cuando se contabiliza el cobro y vuelca a GL tal cual (Copy-Paste). La fecha del tipo de cambio es 31/07/2017 y viene así desde el cobro y su reversión, aunque esté posteada la reversión en agosto, el tipo de cambio de la reversión es de julio. Cualquier cosa que necesite, no dude en comentárnoslo. Gracias. Un cordial saludo. Soporte Sistemas Financieros.

column6: LINUX_sun - ibclogec2.ib : Swap area occupied 93.74%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGro
column11: Issue: ELK- swap memory was almost full on the ibclogec2.ib client node Analysis: Elasticsearch client nodes having a light memory leak and after running for 1 or 2 months, they start consuming swap space quickly. Hence swap memory was almost full on one of the client node. Business Impact: We need to get the client node into elastic search cluster as soon as possible as it can effect the request and response from the Kibana and users might have problem is searching logs & indices in Kibana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on ibclogec2.ib client node and it rejoined the ELK cluster.

column6: Escalado Job: LINUX_ibm - El job: X25OBIM2 con OrderID: 2y12v del DataCenter: CTM_SERVER en la maqu
column11: Issue: Ha fallado el proceso X25OBIM2 porque no ha ejecutado el proceso X25OLST del que controla la condición. Impact: Medio, al no ejecutarse el X25OLST se retrasa la entrega del fichero IB-MERGER-LOADSTATS al proceso que lo explota y por tanto el producto final. Root Cause: El X25OLST no se ejecuto porque el proceso X25OI21 no tenia activiada la condicion FICI281-OK 1601. Steps Taken: Añadir la condicion FICI281-OK 1601 para que se ejecute el proceso X25OI21 y se ejecute el proceso X25OLST. Una vez ejecutado el X25OLST se borra el X25OBIM2 fallado.

Errores SAC 99999999- Después de tres intentos sin obtener SAC, un programa los pone a 9999999 (es una antigua petición de Administración y Comercial). Tener SAC a 99999999 significa que no se ha podido obtener un SAC normal ni tampoco se va a poder obtener, es decir, son errores irrecuperables. Errores de cia 060 - Son EMD's con un SAC aparentemente correcto. Desde TKT no podemos saber por qué Ib Express no los acepta.

column11: [29/1/2018] NIIT.prani Issue: No se envía CC en transacciones por Netplus – Authentication NO Impact: One PNR Impacted Resolution: transactions with result INT_PET_INI_AUT_RESP_INVALIDA are not errors actually. These are the genuine ones. We also observed that these errors occurred even before the date we mentioned (January 17,2018). 1/22/2018 5:37:33 PM, NIIT.prani, We have received the below update from netplus and we have updated the same to business as well. "These kind of transactions with result INT_PET_INI_AUT_RESP_INVALIDA are not errors. Transactions receiving the PARes message from the card issuing bank = N or U do not continue according to the follow table defined by Iberia because: • Validate Authentication / PARes status N ? Verified by Visa Card Enrolled: Unsuccessful Authentication • Validate Authentication / PARes status U ? Issue: In Semi-automatic notifications" that are dated January 11th , although user have "Rejected" them every day, they go out again by email. Impact: User was getting email alerts again and again for semi-automatic notification for same rejected flight. Analysis: As per analysis in lower environment there are many tables are impacted (dependant) by rejecting flight list. As per business logic user has to choose the reject cause option from the menu(Sin motive IB8xxx). After that related data will be update and delete from the tables e.g. ibc_notifications,ibc_semiaut_notif_pending,IBC_GROUPS_TAB,ibc_failed_notifications. Issue: The scheduled job failed as the previous day load was still running. Impact : Minimum impact as the data window is 'sysdate -3 ' so there is no data loss. Analysis: The job on 17th Jan 2018 was in running state because of which the next scheduled job (18th Jan 2018 &19th jan 2018) failed.This job took more than 60 hours and still did not finish. This job has a data windoe of 'sysdate -3 ' so the job can be killed and can be rerun. Resolution: The running job's session was killed and the sceduled job for the next executed .The load was successful.

column11: Issue: 2 pax were unable to check-in/ Impact: It was the case of two pax hence there was not much impact. I see that the confirmed segments are now not available and only an open segment is there, so in case this PNR is re-used please use UDNU25 ref. No further action from support. [2] For user BEST/ANDREW This pax was not able to check-in earlier due to missed UPG information from the host(Resiber). Please see the attached screenshot naming ‘Mr.BEST-1”. But later when the correct information was provided by the host, the pax successfully completed the check-in operation and the boarding pass was generated perfectly. Please see the screenshot naming “Mr.Best-2”. We believe that it does not require any further action. Issue: Automtion 'IB_Proceso_Bajas_FULL_Triggered' failed Analysis: We checked the bajas file on the FTP and found that the bajas file was empty and as well as delayed due to which the automation did not run. Impact: If this automation will not run then unsubscriber list will not be ingest the data extension and also subscriber will receive unwanted notifications so they might escalate Iberia for that and there may be a huge impact on the brand itself. Resolution: We raised a case to Salesforce Help Team to ingest the empty file Through automation, so the team enabled the empty business rule and stop parameter for import activity to process the empty file. Now the automation ran successfully for the empty file as well.

Issue: During the archival process of old snapshot backup 'backup-2017.12.04', the snapshot was not deleted from the snapshot repository of NFS_backup drive. Analysis: We checked in the logs and found that that backup was archived however the step of deletion of backup from the snapshot repository did not takes place. Business Impact: High disk usage in NFS_backup drive can prevent future snapshots to be created. And ELK cluster can become unstable if backup policies don't work well. Resolution: We checked with the Linux team if the archival of backup.2017.12.04 is present. After confirmation , we deleted this snapshot from the NFS_DRIVE

column6: LINUX_sun - ERROR en APLICACI?N=IBConecta, CI=HUB003. Avisar Oncall CRM
column11: <ISSUE>:: Errors in application , application was giving intermittent errors.The logs genarted by Ibconecta showed that there were connectivity errors. <IMPACT>:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database and hence no new notifications from IbConecta <ANALYSIS>:: As per the support document incident we request DBA team to check the errors, we check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors but more often than not the connectivity is restored itself. <STEPS TAKEN TO RESOLVE>:: As said, we moitored the database for a while and the connectivity was restored. We checked in the logs to verify the connection. <PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? (Yes, No).>:: NO <CAN THIS INCIDENT BE PREVENTED? (Yes, No)> :: No, Its an intermittent issue, when the databse connectivity is lost and Ibconnecta keeps polling for the connection.We had also asked DBS to increase the Pool size which might prevent this issue.

column6: OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT
column11: Issue: Error encountered during execution of IB Card Assignment out File. Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds data of the Card Assignment points, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Avios points against their Iberia Cards. Analysis: File arrived late hence the load plan failed.Therefore manually re ran the load plan to successfully send the IB Card Assignment file to IB Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for IB Card Assignment file to successfully process the load.

column6: Oracle BI Publisher Notification: [Boris report Weekly new]: Job was failed.
column11: Issue: Oracle BI Publisher Notification: [Boris report Weekly new]: Job was failed. Business Impact: User's are not able to recieve the schedule report having the claims data. Analysis: The “Boris” Report job has failed on 15/01/2018. We have analyzed that the issue is with the 09/01/2018 data. There is a record against 9th Jan 2018 where the Customer Name field is having special character in it due to which the report is failing due to “Rendering Document” error. Resolution: The special character needs to be removed from the field value from the source.
